# Git push on Windows (agents)

Before `git push` in any ReactWoo repo:

1. Run `git remote get-url origin`. If URL starts with `https://`, either:
   - `git remote set-url origin git@github.com:reactwoo/<repo>.git`, or
   - push explicitly: `git push git@github.com:reactwoo/<repo>.git main`
2. **Never** chain `commit && tag && push` on Windows.
3. Use **one standalone push command**:

```bash
GIT_SSH_COMMAND="ssh -o BatchMode=yes -o ConnectTimeout=15" git push origin main
```

Release (branch + tag, one push): append `"vVERSION"` to that command.

## Stop — do not waste tokens retrying

- Push **hangs with no output** → stop after ~30s; report repo name + remote URL. Do not repeat the same push.
- Exit **139** or **-1073741819** → retry **once** in a new shell only; then stop and report.
- Push **multiple repos** → **sequentially**, not in parallel loops.

Verify: `git fetch origin && git status -sb` (no `[ahead N]`).

Full doc: `docs/git-push-windows.md`.
